\par\par \b \uc2 Childish lawmakers   \b0\par\par\uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  plenary session Monday on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's emergency liquidity credits to distressed banks during the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis only strengthened \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  frustration over the lack of sense of urgency among the childish and trifling lawmakers regarding the nation's problems.   \par \uc2 682 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 February 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The eight members of the Cabinet who represented President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono, led by chief economics minister Boediono, should have been annoyed at having to waste several hours of their precious working time at the circus at the House.   \par \par \uc2 The House session, which was marked by the walkout of dozens of House members, a flurry of interruptions and even a strange call for a hunger strike, predictably produced nothing likely to help solve the situation.   \par \par \uc2 There was virtually nothing new in the government's explanation of the controversial liquidity credits (estimated at Rp 144.50 trillion or $16 billion) because the questions the House submitted to the President only showed how ignorant most House members are of the real issues behind what is commonly known as the "BLBI scandal".   \par \par \uc2 In fact, the House decision early last December on a motion to question the President on the BLBI was a grossly misguided political move. If the House members are really serious about exercising their constitutional right to check on the latest developments in the handling of the BLBI case they should have summoned the finance minister, the attorney general and the state police chief. It has been these three Cabinet members who have been handling the 10-year-old BLBI case.   \par \par \uc2 Making a political issue out of the BLBI case will create only a new source of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at a time when both the House and the government are under pressure to complete dozens of pieces of \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  badly needed to strengthen the democratic process and deepen \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms.   \par \par \uc2 Summoning the President to explain the circumstances and procedures for the extension of the liquidity credits will only waste House and government resources.   \par \par \uc2 If the House insists on demanding the President personally give answers to the questions House members raise in light of their right of inquiry, such \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  hearings will become largely meaningless political circuses amid an increasingly gloomy \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to the impact of skyrocketing oil prices and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The liquidity credit problem is entirely a law-enforcement issue.   \par \par \uc2 As the government recounted at the House session, 23 of the 43 large debtors (former owners of distressed banks) who received liquidity credits during the height of the banking crisis in 1997-1999 had resolved once and for all their debts under closing agreements with the government which were signed between 2002 and 2004.   \par \par \uc2 The closing agreements themselves were concluded after the government and independent audits ascertained that the value the assets pledged by the debtors was considered sufficient and the legal status of the assets was clear. This debt resolution process itself was based on directives issued by the People's \b \highlight22\uc2 Legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  Assembly, the highest \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making body.   \par \par \uc2 Questioning again the agreements with these 23 debtors would cause legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  because they had ceded their assets to the now-defunct Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) to repay their debts, and most of these assets had been sold by IBRA to domestic and foreign investors.   \par \par \uc2 It would have been much more productive for the House to focus its attention and oversight on the handling of the remaining 20 big debtors. House members should quiz the attorney general and state police about the latest developments in the investigations or prosecutions of the ten big debtors the government has classified as "uncooperative".   \par \par \uc2 The House should grill the finance minister, who is in charge of recovering liquidity credits from 10 other big debtors who are categorized as cooperative to ascertain as to why the debt collection has been so slow.   \par \par \uc2 The government also has yet to explain what legal measures it has so far taken to follow up the report of the Supreme Audit Agency in 1999 which alleged that the bulk of the Rp 144.5 trillion emergency liquidity credits had been misused by their recipients.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080214e42e0000l\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 BI Prioritizes to Control Inflation   \b0\par\par\uc2 365 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 February 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) claims to have prepared several instruments to improve domestic monetary policies and to secure inflation targets for 2008 and 2009.   \par \par \uc2 The government fixes the inflation target in the 2008 Revised State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 6.5%, while at the working meeting with the House Commission XI the target is still fixed at 6%.   \par \par \uc2 BI Governor Burhanuddin Abdullah revealed measures to secure inflation were necessary to maintain Indonesia's competitiveness amidst \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation.   \par \par \uc2 Another instrument prepared by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  was by changing the mechanism to establish interest rate from fixed rate to variable rate.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he continued, had been applied since two weeks ago and aimed to provide larger flexibility in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities.   \par \par \uc2 "We view that the impact of the currency exchange rate fluctuation on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the time of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  instability is unpredictable in the long run," he said after meeting with President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 He added various global issues, such as soaring commodity prices and the sub-prime mortgage case in the US, were still posing threats.   \par \par \uc2 One of the policies taken by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to control inflation, he inserted, was by maintaining BI rate at 8% following the realization of inflation in January at 1.77%.   \par \par \uc2 Inflationary pressures in several Asian countries, such as South Korea and Thailand, had also made it difficult for their central banks to reduce the spread between the Fed rate and their domestic ones.   \par \par \uc2 Prices on consumer level in Srilanka, as reported by Bloomberg, skyrocketed by 20% in January. Inflations also increased in China, India, and Australia following the decline of the manufacture sectors in those countries declined in January.   \par \par \uc2 Price increase is a challenge for \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -makers in Asia and Europe to create balance between \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown and inflation.   \par \par \uc2 Former \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -maker at Bank of England Charlers Goodhart explained that some central banks less favored cutting \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and instead would let their currencies to improve.   \par \par \uc2 The Consumer Price Index in South Korea in January recorded the three-year high in January triggered by the industry goods and fuel price hikes.   \par \par \uc2 By Tri D. Pamenan & Ratna Ariyanti   \par \par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080218e42g0005o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
