\par\par \b \uc2 Stronger footing for  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 693 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 February 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The 6.3 percent full-year growth for 2007, the highest over the last decade, combined with the higher credit rating given by Fitch Ratings and the persistently bullish sentiment on the Indonesia Stock Exchange, could give the country the confidence needed to weather the weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The robust growth, as announced by the Central Statistics Agency on Friday, though lower than the government expectation of 6.4 to 6.5 percent, will surely place the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on a stronger footing in facing the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the international financial market and the global credit crunch.   \par \par \uc2 On a quarterly basis, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  did contract in the last quarter, but that was expected by many analysts due to the devastating impact of the international financial turbulence set off by the U.S. subprime mortgage crisis in the second half.   \par \par \uc2 The damage inflicted by the negative external factors could have been more extensive had it not been for the high pace of government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which usually reaches its peak during the last quarter of the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. Some analysts estimate more than 60 percent of the government investment \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  last year was spent during the fourth quarter alone.   \par \par \uc2 True, as many analysts said, the 6.3 percent growth was a disappointment to the millions of jobseekers due to its failure to generate a large number of jobs. That is because the growth rate of the manufacturing and agricultural sectors -- among the largest employers -- was lower than other sectors such as transportation, communications, trading, utilities and financial services.   \par \par \uc2 One day before the Central Statistics Agency announced the final 2007 GDP growth rate, Fitch Ratings raised Indonesia's credit rating to its highest level in a decade, citing the bright outlook for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , increasing international \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  and record prices of natural resource-based commodities. This will certainly have a positive impact on the government's borrowing costs and investor confidence in the long-term prospects of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Also encouraging is the fact that the main levers of growth -- consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , investment and exports -- are running at a high pace. Record prices for natural resource-based commodities such as palm oil, rubber, cocoa and coal in the international market have fueled stronger consumer demand among the rural households who account for almost half of the total population.   \par \par \uc2 Business \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , spurred by the 4.75 percentage point reduction in the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark interest rate since the middle of 2006, has also expanded significantly, and so has bank lending.   \par \par \uc2 We share the optimism of Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) chief executive officer Erry Firmansyah, who foresaw a rise of at least 30 percent in the IDX composite index this year, as against the 52 percent gain in 2007.   \par \par \uc2 The long list of state and private companies gearing up for initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offerings and bond issues this year will deepen and broaden the capital market, thereby increasing its role as a source of funds for businesses, in addition to banks.   \par \par \uc2 However, the rosy outlook for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could turn sour if the revisions the government is finalizing for its 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , in anticipating the negative impact of the weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and high food and energy prices, are not seen by the market as credible.   \par \par \uc2 The most crucial factor for \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability is how the government controls fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which could balloon to more than $20 billion this year without a reduction in consumption or an increase in fuel prices.   \par \par \uc2 The government therefore should see to it that its plan to ration the sales of subsidized gasoline to private cars through the introduction of Smart Cards -- though not the best and most effective measure to slash \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- achieves its target of cutting \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  by at least $10 billion.   \par \par \uc2 Equally important is that the implementation of the more than $17 billion in investment the government plans to make this year in basic infrastructure runs smoothly and on schedule.   \par \par \uc2 If the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  amendments fail to project sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management, the development of infrastructure, already several years behind schedule, is not accelerated and badly needed \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms fail to materialize, the market will severely punish our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080218e42i0000n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
