\par\par \b \uc2 BI governor candidates   \b0\par\par\uc2 700 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 February 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono apparently wants the new governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) to make a clean break from the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's scandal-tainted past. And by excluding the eight members of the current BI board of governors from the candidacy for the new BI governor, the President also does not want to risk any political turbulence or protracted nomination process.   \par \par \uc2 This, we think, is the strongest message Yudhoyono wanted to convey by nominating two complete outsiders -- Agus Martowardojo, currently chief executive officer of state-owned  \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , the country's largest bank, and Raden Pardede, deputy chief of the state-owned Assets Management Company -- as candidates for the new governor of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 There is indeed a great risk for the President to submit to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  candidates who might later be implicated in the BI fund scandal or other corruption cases if he nominated career central bankers.   \par \par \uc2 Thus far, already 17 senior BI executives, including the current governor Burhanuddin Abdullah, and former executives have either been banned from traveling overseas by the Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) or declared suspects in corruption.   \par \par \uc2 The list of suspects could increase as the KPK intensifies its investigation of the corruption case.   \par \par \uc2 The problem is the alleged misuse of more than Rp 100 billion (US$10.7 million) in BI funds for legal fees to former BI governors and deputy governors, and for funding \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  opinion campaigns related to then proposed amendments of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law in 2003-2004, is not the only scandal hitting the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  right now.   \par \par \uc2 The current House investigation of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's liquidity credits to the banking industry during the height of the financial crisis in 1997-1999 could also implicate more BI executives in corruption cases. The House seemed determined to push forward with investigation into the Supreme Audit Agency's report in 2000 that the bulk of the Rp 145.5 trillion in emergency liquidity credits extended by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had either been misused by banks or improperly issued by BI.   \par \par \uc2 But the selection process at the House could become very difficult because neither of the two candidates appeared to be favored or supported by any of the major factions at the House. But we think it is worthwhile for the President to risk political wrangling with the House because his primary objective is to improve good governance at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 In terms of technical competence, experience, managerial capability and international networking, Miranda S. Goeltom, currently BI's senior deputy governor, should have been a strong candidate, especially because she also commands strong support of a major faction at the House. But she could, like many other BI executives, be implicated later in any of the allegations of corruption and scandal currently beleaguering the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 By law, the House can throw out the two candidates the President nominated, and in that case, Yudhoyono should nominate new candidates, a protracted process that certainly could not be completed by mid-May when Burhanuddin Abdullah's term ends.   \par \par \uc2 There is actually no strong reason for the House not to choose either one of the candidates because both Martowardojo and Pardede meet the basic requirements for a BI governor as stipulated in the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law: high integrity, technical competence, managerial capability and leadership.   \par \par \uc2 These requirements are indeed necessary for the leaders of such a politically independent institution as the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which functions as the bedrock of the monetary system, the guardian of monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the arbiter of the financial system. The BI chief should have high integrity and high ability to stand up against political pressures or interference from the government or the House.   \par \par \uc2 Any faction at the House intending to create political bickering over the candidates is well-advised to realize the selection process of the new BI chief should be completed on time, especially now amid the global financial \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Protracted political debates about the BI governor candidate, especially if Burhanuddin's successor cannot be selected by mid-May, could affect BI monetary management capability with all its damaging repercussions on the rupiah, anti-inflation measures and bank supervision.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080219e42j0000l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
