\par\par \b \uc2 Battered  \highlight22\uc2 central bank \highlight\uc2  faces  \highlight22\uc2 policy \highlight\uc2  dilemma   \b0\par\par\uc2 Winarno Zain , Jakarta   \par \uc2 1,073 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 March 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The investigation of graft cases involving the governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Burhanuddin Abdullah, is taking place at a very unfortunate time.   \par \par \uc2 It is a time when the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is facing difficult challenges, and rising inflation and the prospect of slower growth needs an immediate response in the form of new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Under such conditions, it is difficult for BI to formulate an effective \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  response. The current graft investigation of its governor is a moral blow to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and the investigation by the anti-corruption body (KPK) is draining the time and resources of the BI leadership, making it difficult for them to focus on their main job.   \par \par \uc2 Inflation came down to 0.6 percent in February from 1.7 percent in January. Yet, the year-on-year rate in February was 7.4 percent, slightly higher than in the previous month. Food price indices are still rising at 12 percent, much faster than the Consumer Price Index (CPI). While the ongoing rise in food prices could plateau in the next two or three months because of the rice harvest, inflation caused by higher oil prices will negate any impact it might have.   \par \par \uc2 A growth in inflation in the coming months is indicated by changes in the Wholesale Price Index, which tends to predict the future trends of the CPI. There have been significant increases in the WPI in the last three months. The WPI had been growing at 11 percent during most of 2007, but jumped to 15 percent in October and then to 22 percent in December.   \par \par \uc2 The fact the WPI is increasing at three times the rate of the CPI might mean producers and distributors have not yet passed added costs onto consumers. Growing competition in the face of a weaker \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  might prompt them to withhold price increases. They would rather accept the profit squeeze than lose customers. But this can not go on for much longer. As their prices start eating away at their profits, they will eventually have to raise prices, which will push the CPI upward.   \par \par \uc2 Although the growth in bank loans in recent months was widely predicted, its growth rate deserves tighter monitoring from BI, as this could pose a risk for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability. The growth in bank loans accelerated in the last quarter of 2007, and by December 2007 it grew 25 percent, up from 14 percent in early 2007.   \par \par \uc2 Investment has been well supported by the increase in bank loans, and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence has gradually been restored. Investment as a component of GDP grew 9.2 percent last year after a sluggish growth of 3 percent the year before. In fact, investment in the fourth quarter of 2007 grew 12 percent, the highest rate of the year, although it was returning from poor levels in 2006.   \par \par \uc2 But the rapid growth in bank lending has not been accompanied by a flurry of bank deposits, with negative real \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to blame. Bank deposits are growing at only 15 percent, far lower than the growth in lending. If this trend continues, banks will have trouble funding their loans.   \par \par \uc2 Some banks have entered the money market seeking additional funding, and we will soon see more banks issuing bonds. Timing could not be worse -- at the same time the government, faced with an increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is floating bonds in the money market in a big way. It could create "overcrowding" in the money market, which will in turn push up \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The rapid growth of bank loans also could pose a risk for loans that are not peforming.   \par \par \uc2 The risk of conducting business in Indonesia remains high because of slow \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, infrastructure problems in many parts of the country and because regulations for doing business are still unclear.   \par \par \uc2 It is important for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to be more alert to this risk and to vigorously supervise the banks. Unfortunately, the current situation BI is in could adversely affect its ability to supervise them.   \par \par \uc2 With the current BI governor facing investigation on graft cases and the president and the House still selecting a new governor, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  is practically being led by a lame duck governor. It is difficult for BI to make any important decisions, such as on monetary policies, which will have to be delayed until the new governor is appointed.   \par \par \uc2 This means \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development in Indonesia will be drifting without direction for some time. This is unfortunate given rapid changes in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  need a quick \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  response.   \par \par \uc2 How long can BI maintain its loose monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the face of mounting inflationary pressures? BI still expects inflation will ease in coming months, as measures to stem the rise in food prices, such as reducing import tariffs and stepping up domestic production, take effect.   \par \par \uc2 Slowing down the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would also take some of the steam off inflation, and could plausibly allow the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to maintain its current approach. But instead, averting a slow \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a bit problematic for BI. In the hope of reviving the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , BI has been loosening its monetary policies since 2006.   \par \par \uc2 But the effect of monetary loosening on investment is still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . In 2007, investment constituted 24 percent of GDP, a figure that did not change from 2006, and is still far below the 30 percent rate achieved before 1996. It is clear that a loose monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , at least in Indonesia, has not resulted in any significant effect on investment.   \par \par \uc2 Other factors, like the investment climate, may play a larger role in boosting investment. Monetary policies designed to revitalize investment could hardly achieve their objective if infrastructure is in a poor condition, and regulatory frameworks are \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 In such a climate, lax monetary policies are only risking higher inflation. That is why loosening monetary policies to revive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is a questionable strategy.   \par \par \uc2 BI might have to think twice before further reducing its \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The challenge for BI leadership is how to design an immediate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  response to address some critical issues facing the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . With the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stance being weakened by government inaction in the face of a higher \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it is necessary for BI to pick up its act to prevent macro \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  instability. Otherwise, it will be difficult to stop the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  drifting downward.   \par \par \uc2 The writer is an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  analyst.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080314e43e0000o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
