\par\par \b \uc2 The fight for a new BI governor   \b0\par\par\uc2 With inflationary pressures persistently strong, and stocks and currencies tending to fluctuate wildly, a protracted political process of selecting a new \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor to replace Burhanuddin Abdullah, who will end his term in mid-May, could adversely affect the market perception of our macroeconomic stability.   \par \uc2 699 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 March 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono therefore should immediately come up with new candidates for \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) governor to replace the two nominees voted down by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  last Tuesday. And given the animosity that surrounded the House screening of those two candidates, the President should nominate at least three candidates both from inside and outside the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to give the House a wider choice and to expedite the political process.   \par \par \uc2 It is a futile and time-wasting exercise for the government to demand the House clearly account for its vote against the two candidates, Agus Martowardoyo and Raden Pardede. The market is nervously waiting to know who will be the new leader at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  now that its governor Abdullah, already a corruption suspect, is under investigation by the Corruption Eradication Commission.   \par \par \uc2 If foreign capital leaves the country because of political bickering and concerns over BI monetary management capability, it will adversely affect the rupiah and stock market where foreign portfolio investors play an important role.   \par \par \uc2 By nominating complete outsiders to the top post at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the President seemed focused on selecting a new governor of impeccable integrity since the outgoing governor had been declared a corruption suspect and there are several corruption cases currently under investigation that could implicate many incumbent \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  executives.   \par \par \uc2 The House had no doubt about the high integrity and technical competence of the two candidates -- Martowardoyo, currently president of state-owned  \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , the country's largest bank, and Pardede, the chairman of the government-sponsored Forum for Financial Market Stability and vice president of the state asset management company PPA -- but most House members saw them as too closely linked with the President to be able to function independently.   \par \par \uc2 The House was right in demanding the BI chief not only have strong leadership but also be able to stand up against political pressures or interference from the government, especially in view of the upcoming general elections and presidential elections next year.   \par \par \uc2 One may argue the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  faced an even worse situation than it does now when its then governor Sjahril Sabirin was jailed for six months in 2002 and was eventually convicted by the Central Jakarta district court with a three-year jail sentence, yet BI worked normally and Sabirin resumed his functions until the end of his term in mid-2003 after he was acquitted by the Supreme Court of all charges.   \par \par \uc2 But given the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the global financial market and the corruption cases currently engulfing the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , we urgently need a new \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor not only with impeccable integrity and strong leadership qualities. The candidate also must be a brilliant macroeconomist with extensive international networks, a good \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  speaker, an able chief executive and an international diplomat.   \par \par \uc2 These requirements are necessary for the leader of such a politically independent institution as the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which functions as the bedrock of the monetary system, the guardian of monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the arbiter of the financial system.   \par \par \uc2 There are several candidates that meet the criteria, including the current chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister Boediono, who himself was formerly a BI deputy governor, and several members of the current BI board of governors, especially senior Deputy Governor Miranda S. Goeltom.   \par \par \uc2 At the present time when new crises seem to emerge on a daily basis, when the outlook for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is bleak, consumer confidence is fragile and better cooperation and coordination between the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary authorities is even more imperative, a weak governor at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  could send the wrong signal to the market.   \par \par \uc2 The role of BI is especially crucial for our macroeconomic stability and growth because different from the central banks in other countries, BI is tasked with multiple missions of maintaining the stability of the rupiah and general price rates (low inflation) and supervising the banking industry.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080324e43o0003a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
