\par\par \b \uc2 Work it baby! New gyms are popping up everywhere   \b0\par\par\uc2 Prodita Sabarini , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 1,038 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 March 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 7\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Ten years ago, Jakartans went to the mall with credit cards and cash, now they may also have a gym membership card in their wallets.   \par \par \uc2 Thanks partly to an ever-increasing focus on healthier living and partly to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , fitness clubs are popping up all over Jakarta -- many within malls -- and there are more on the way.   \par \par \uc2 Celebrity Fitness, which started in Indonesia and also has outlets in Malaysia;  \uc2 Fitness First\uc2 , a chain of gym clubs in the U.K, Europe, Australia, and the Asia-Pacific region; and the international chain Gold's Gym are all convinced the market can support the added gym space.   \par \par \uc2 By the end of 2008, the chains will have a combined membership of more than 80,000 people.   \par \par \uc2 Celebrity Fitness has nine outlets throughout the city, having increased its membership from 4,500, when it first opened five years ago in Plaza EX on Jl. Thamrin, to 50,000 today.   \par \par \uc2 Fitness First\uc2 , which opened in 2005, has seven outlets, with 28,000 members. While Gold's Gym now has four outlets, with 6,000 members.   \par \par \uc2 These figures still exclude hotel gyms and no-frills clubs such as Club Ade Rai, which was founded by prominent bodybuilder Ade Rai. Ade said there were 15 Ade Rai gyms in the city.   \par \par \uc2 He said the rise of gym culture in Jakarta was a result of increased awareness among people of the need for healthier lifestyles.   \par \par \uc2 Gyms have muscled their way into the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  consciousness as people fear they are suffering the consequences of living in a polluted and overcrowded city like Jakarta, as well as being glued to their computers and televisions day after day.   \par \par \uc2 This is combined with high stress levels and poor diets -- people are breaking away from the "three meals a day structure" in favor of foods that are calorific.   \par \par \uc2 The need for fitness centers in the city is obvious, Ade said.   \par \par \uc2 "We have more access to information from the media about healthy living; we have role models in the form of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  figures who go to the gym; we see movies starring well-built men and women; and more fitness centers are opening up in the city," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Ade said the rise of fitness center happened during the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis of 1997 and 1998.   \par \par \uc2 "It's interesting to note that when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was in havoc that was the time when people started to get more interested in fitness," he said.   \par \par \uc2 "At that time, people were stressed and there was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in business. What they could control was their bodies, so there was an increase in the demand for fitness centers," he said.   \par \par \uc2 This was observed by business players in the health industry, who consequently opened more gyms, Ade said.   \par \par \uc2 Celebrity fitness regional manager Hendra Nugraha, however, believes the chain paved the way to make the gyms-in-malls concept work, from a business point of view.   \par \par \uc2 "We changed the whole concept of gyms in Jakarta," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Before Celebrity Fitness opened its first outlet in EX shopping center in 2003, all gyms in Jakarta were either in hotels or their own buildings.   \par \par \uc2 "Fitness centers were seen as places for men with the buff bodies of soldiers. Our fitness centers are for ordinary people who want leaner bodies like celebrities," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The gym prides itself on using local celebrities to promote its image but is also known for its aggressive marketing efforts.   \par \par \uc2 "This (Celebrity Fitness) changed the image of gyms, encouraging both men and women to join up," Hendra said.   \par \par \uc2 Either way, fitness magazine Muscle Indonesia's chief editor Teddy Tjahjadi said the soaring number of gyms in Jakarta today was just the beginning.   \par \par \uc2 "Even with new gyms opening up, the number of people going to the gym is still only around 2 to 3 percent of the total market," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He said the concept of setting up gyms in malls was "brilliant".   \par \par \uc2 "Now, whenever there's a crowd there's a gym."   \par \par \uc2 But Celebrity Fitness, which has 20 clubs at present, isn't the only one wooing locals bent on getting buff.   \par \par \uc2 Fitness First\uc2 , which has more than 500 clubs worldwide, opened its first club at Plaza Semanggi in 2005. It has the simple philosophy of providing affordable fitness and aims to help adults of any age exercise correctly.   \par \par \uc2 Hendra said Celebrity's focus was on keeping members entertained. Its clubs have funky interiors and pop music is constantly played.   \par \par \uc2 "Our fitness centers do not only serve as a place to work out but also as a place to socialize," he said. "After work you can go to the mall, go shopping and then work out," Hendra said.   \par \par \uc2 In 2006, Gold's gym, which is dubbed "the mecca of bodybuilding" expanded to Jakarta.   \par \par \uc2 Teddy, who distributes Muscle Indonesia in the three fitness centers, said each had its own character.   \par \par \uc2 "Celebrity fitness is more for socializing. Members come to the gym, socialize, work out, socialize, and then go home.  \uc2 Fitness First\uc2  is more for the solitary people, who comes to the gym just to work out; while Gold's Gym is more for the people who are serious about building their bodies," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Teddy said people were influenced by their friends, doctors, or even the movies, to join a gym.   \par \par \uc2 "Western movies have brought attention not only to the gym itself, but to the body in general," he said.   \par \par \uc2 "And with the competition between fitness centers, it's relatively inexpensive to join a gym."   \par \par \uc2 Celebrity Fitness' monthly fees range between Rp 429,000 and Rp 495,000,  \uc2 Fitness First\uc2 's between Rp 350,000 and Rp 500,000 and Gold's Gym's between Rp 250,000 and Rp 350,000.   \par \par \uc2 The first edition of Muscle Indonesia was launched in August 2007. Teddy said it was aimed at the growing population of gym members.   \par \par \uc2 Ade said the fitness industry was expanding not only in terms of gyms. "Magazines that talk about fitness, gym wear, food supplements, healthy food restaurants -- you name it. The market is growing," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The question is, are there enough fitness professionals in the city to go around?   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080330e43u00021\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
