\par\par \b \uc2 Boediono to lead  \highlight22\uc2 central bank \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 602 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 April 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono's nomination of the incumbent Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Boediono, as the new governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a breakthrough in the deadlock over the selection of a new leader for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Boediono, more than anyone else, is the best candidate for the job, both because he is politically acceptable to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and because he can meet all the tough requirements in the face of the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the international financial market and weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 He is also a greatly capable macroeconomist with extensive international networks and experience, including as a governor of the World Bank.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono is a good speaker, an able chief executive and an international diplomat with a calm and careful attitude in getting things accomplished.   \par \par \uc2 His knowledge and blend of experiences--he was finance minister during Megawati Soekarnoputri's administration in 2001-2004, a deputy governor at \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 1996-1998 and state minister for development planning--is especially suitable now Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary authorities must strengthen cooperation and coordination in a high inflationary environment.   \par \par \uc2 Most importantly, however, is that the 65-year-old Wharton-trained economist commands impeccable integrity and competence and is highly respected both in international and domestic circles.   \par \par \uc2 All this will greatly help the integrity and credibility of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  which has been beleaguered by several corruption cases with its outgoing governor Burhanuddin Abdullah and two other senior executives already declared as corruption suspects.   \par \par \uc2 Despite Boediono's deep involvement with the Yudhoyono government over the past two years, there should be no doubt of the political independence of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  under his leadership.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono is the kind of person who is able to stand firm against political pressure or interference from the government or any members of the Cabinet, especially in view of the upcoming general elections and presidential elections next year.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono's nomination has left the President with the tough job of selecting an equally capable person for a new chief economics minister to replace him.   \par \par \uc2 However, Yudhoyono rightly gave top priority to the selection of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  chief to replace Burhanuddin, who will end his term mid-May.   \par \par \uc2 The requirements of the new chief economics minister are equally as stringent as those of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor position. Boediono's successor should be capable of maintaining the credibility and consistency of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 -\b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  making and implementation.   \par \par \uc2 The new coordinating minister should be able to comprehend the importance of a coherent and credible strategy which outlines how the various individual policies hang together, showing on the path toward the broad direction in which the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is being steered.   \par \par \uc2 The recruitment process for the new coordinating minister position should, however, be easier as the selection process is entirely under his control. The President is not required to enter the "political jungle" at the House.   \par \par \uc2 So, all in all, the selection process at the House should be smooth because, in terms of political acceptability, integrity, credibility and experiences in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary management and international networks, Boediono is far better than the two previous candidates--Agus Martowardoyo, chief executive officer of  \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , and Raden Pardede, vice president of the state Asset Management Company--who were both voted down by the House.   \par \par \uc2 The House -- and especially factions which are still disappointed with the single candidate that may try to block Boediono -- are well advised to realize the adverse impact of a protracted political process of selecting a new \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  chief on the government's macroeconomic management capability.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080403e4430000l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
