\par\par \b \uc2 Only credible contingency measures can reassure the market   \b0\par\par\uc2 Vincent Lingga , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 727 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 April 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati told an emergency news conference after an unscheduled limited Cabinet session on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  chaired by President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono last Thursday that the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was under control and that escalating inflationary pressures were manageable despite the soaring food prices and fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 In a stronger bid to reassure the market, Sri Mulyani put the government's money where its mouth is, stating the government would buy back in cash its bonds maturing between 2008 and 2013.   \par \par \uc2 However, the market will remain jittery, nervously waiting for concrete, credible measures to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability and check the runaway inflation, which cumulatively reached 3.41 percent during the first quarter alone, as against the 6.5 percent inflation target for the whole year.   \par \par \uc2 Year-on-year inflation in March surged to 8.2 percent, already higher than \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark short-term interest rate of 8 percent.   \par \par \uc2 No wonder that investors, already skittish due to the global financial turmoil, became more worried over what they perceive as higher sovereign risks of the government.   \par \par \uc2 This is reflected in the increase in the risk premium on Indonesia's international bonds to 300 basis points (over the U.S. Treasury bonds) last month from 130 bp last year.   \par \par \uc2 The government's domestic borrowing costs also have risen, as shown by the increase in the yield on rupiah bonds to more than 12 percent from around 9 percent last year.   \par \par \uc2 This is truly worrisome because the government plans to raise Rp 117.80 trillion (US$12.8 billion) from rupiah and dollar bonds this year to help plug its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  hole.   \par \par \uc2 The miserable failure to get a single bid for its zero-coupon bonds auctioned late last month showed how widely different were the government and market perceptions of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook.   \par \par \uc2 The government claims the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation is generally healthy and that the underlying assumptions in the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  are not much different from the reality.   \par \par \uc2 However, the market sees things differently.   \par \par \uc2 Market players believe the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will not be sustainable as long as it remains helplessly strapped to the nasty roller coaster of increasingly costly oil. How could the government still claim the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is anchored on prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management when fuel, power and food \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  will take up more than 23 percent of total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year?   \par \par \uc2 How could the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  be seen as politically viable when energy \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  alone will exceed budgetary appropriations for capital investment and social \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 ?   \par \par \uc2 The state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a communication system, conveying signals to the market and the people in general about behavior, prices, priorities, intentions and commitments. \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms therefore should take particular account of these characteristics.   \par \par \uc2 Even without so many inimical external factors, the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  system is already adversely affected by multiple, converging \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , entrenched patterns of \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 , severe inflation and structural imbalances between expectations and resources.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  system must be built to cope with these realities.   \par \par \uc2 Unfortunately, most of the contingency measures pronounced by the government focus on austerity and high \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  discipline, which sadly have so far been the main weaknesses of the government.   \par \par \uc2 None of the measures is designed to reduce fuel consumption or slash fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , thereby leaving the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  a helpless hostage to the wildly volatile international prices.   \par \par \uc2 Another problem is that the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- more than US$17 billion in budgetary allocations for capital \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year -- may again come in fits and starts, ill-timed and beyond the bureaucratic machinery's digestive powers. Last year, for example, almost 60 percent of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  appropriations for capital expenditures was spent in the last quarter alone.   \par \par \uc2 Without significant progress in \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  execution, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 6.4 percent -- as against 6 percent forecast by the ADB and the World Bank and 6.2 percent by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- will not likely be achieved because private and government consumption remains one of the main drivers of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  expansion, besides investment and exports.   \par \par \uc2 How the government maintains its prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management and implements more concerted efforts to bolster exports and investment to offset the impact of the weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will determine the government sovereign risks and investors' risk appetite regarding its bonds, which in turn will influence the costs of its borrowing.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080407e44700005\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
