\par\par \b \uc2 Revised state  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  still faces  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 559 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 April 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Thursday approved a revised 2008 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  projecting lower growth and a bigger \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid a weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Even after the major changes the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains vulnerable to downside risks as the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is flirting with a deep recession amid a high inflationary environment caused by high energy and food prices.\par \par \uc2 The revised \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  lowers the growth target from 6.8 percent as set in the original \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 6.4 percent and raises the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  by almost 30 percent to Rp 95 trillion (US$10.4 billion).\par \par \uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati said setting macroeconomic assumptions and aggregate revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was like shooting at a moving target.\par \par \uc2 "Therefore, this global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  requires better cooperation between the government and the Parliament in responding to new developments with appropriate and quick contingency measures," Sri Mulyani told the plenary session.\par \par \uc2 The government, Sri Mulyani added, would continue to monitor the situation and had prepared a set of contingency measures to cope with any rapid deterioration of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition.\par \par \uc2 "But we need good cooperation on the part of the House," she said.\par \par \uc2 She said the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  had needed significant revision so the macroeconomic assumptions used for revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimates would be adequately realistic and give the market the right signal on \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  sets aside Rp 13.5 trillion in contingency funds to cope with an unexpected rise in \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  caused by bigger fuel, electricity and food \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  allocations and other expenditures.\par \par \uc2 The minister acknowledged the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  was highly vulnerable to significant changes in oil prices.\par \par \uc2 "The average oil price assumption has been raised to $95 which consequently doubles fuel and electricity \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  to Rp 187 trillion. Things could get worse still if oil prices rise to more than $100 per barrel."\par \par \uc2 She said the government had prepared a set of contingency measures to ready for a potential ballooning of fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including severe restrictions on the use of subsidized gasoline through the application of smart cards.\par \par \uc2 Other macroeconomic assumptions used by the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  include \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark interest rate of 7.5 percent and an average crude oil production of 927,000 barrels per day (bpd).\par \par \uc2 "This crude oil lifting estimate is still rather optimistic given the natural declining output of old wells and because our daily output over the last three days averaged only 916,000 barrels," Sri Mulyani said.\par \par \uc2 Since Indonesia is already a net oil importer, a lower crude oil lifting means larger imports and consequently bigger \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The 2008 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  revisions also raise government borrowing from the domestic and international debt markets (bonds) to Rp 117.8 trillion from the Rp 91.6 trillion originally planned. (uwi)\par \par \uc2 2008 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  <br>\par \par \uc2 Revised Original<br> -------------------------------------------------------------\b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Growth 6.4% 6.8% <br> Inflation 6.5% 6.0% <br> 3-month SBI 7.5% 7.5%<br> Exchange Rate Rp 9,100 Rp 9,100<br> Oil Price $95/barrel $60/barrel<br> Oil Output 927,000 bpd 1,043,000 bpd <br> Total Revenue Rp 895.0 trillion Rp 781.3 trillion<br> Total \b \highlight22\uc2 Spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rp 989.5 trillion Rp 854.6 trillion <br> \b \highlight22\uc2 Deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  Rp 95.0 trillion Rp 73.3 trillion --------------------------------------------------------------- Source: \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080411e44b00009\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
