\par\par \b \uc2 Govt may up fuel prices in June\b0\par\par\uc2 Abdul Khalik and Rendi Akhmad Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 644 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 April 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The government is exploring the possibility of raising fuel prices in June by an average of 28.7 percent in response to skyrocketing fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which many fear may undermine the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 A lawmaker from the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  committee and a businessman close to President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono told The Jakarta Post on Tuesday that all key economics ministers had approved the plan.\par \par \uc2 "It's the President's call now to lay it on the table," the lawmaker said, adding the President's fear of losing popularity ahead of next year's presidential election was the main reason behind the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in fuel prices.\par \par \uc2 Under a proposal that will be discussed further by the President and the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) next month, the price of premium gasoline would be raised to Rp 6,000 (65 U.S. cents) per liter from Rp 4,500.\par \par \uc2 The price of diesel would be set at Rp 5,500 per liter, up from the current Rp 4,300, while kerosene will be raised to Rp 2,500 from Rp 2,000.\par \par \uc2 If fuel prices were raised, it would allow the government to save Rp 25 trillion in \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to the proposal.\par \par \uc2 Under the new oil price assumption in the revised state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  rose from Rp 42 trillion to Rp 126.82 trillion, about 12 percent of the government's Rp 987.48 trillion total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The new scheme is based on an estimate the Indonesian Crude Price (ICP) -- the country's benchmark oil price -- will stand at an average of US$95 a barrel for the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  year.\par \par \uc2 The average ICP price during the first quarter of the year was $103.10 a barrel, while fuel consumption reached 27 percent of this year's 35.5 million kiloliter allocation.\par \par \uc2 The proposal also includes a new mechanism for a direct cash distribution scheme to help cushion low-income Indonesians from the impact of rising fuel prices, which would likely trigger a rise in the prices of other products.\par \par \uc2 "Some Rp 11.5 trillion of the total money saved from the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be given directly to the poor," said the lawmaker.\par \par \uc2 The proposal also includes an assumption of a higher \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  benchmark interest rate at 8.5 percent from the current 8 percent, and a lower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 6 percent from the current forecast of 6.4 percent.\par \par \uc2 "Vice President Jusuf Kalla has already approved the proposal. He will lead some key economics ministers and business representatives to discuss it with the President next month," the businessman said.\par \par \uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati and Energy and Mineral Resources Minister Purnomo Yusgiantoro acknowledged the proposal, saying it was one of the government's options to address the growing fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "It (the proposal) is similar to the story conveyed during the revision of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We will look at all the scenarios to help the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and at the same time reduce negative impacts on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Mulyani told the Post .\par \par \uc2 President Yudhoyono has received pressure from the business community to raise fuel prices in a bid to ensure \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability.\par \par \uc2 Analysts fear that if \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability is not ensured, it could endanger the country's sovereign risk, which would eventually make overseas lending expensive and foreign-direct investment riskier.\par \par \uc2 Kadin officials and a group of local businesspeople renewed calls Tuesday for President Yudhoyono immediately to raise fuel prices to help ease speculation in the financial market.\par \par \uc2 "The market is now speculating on the sustainability of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This will not be good for businesses in trying to accurately formulate business plans. The government should send a signal of certainty," said Kadin chairman Mohamad S. Hidayat.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080430e44u00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
