h they did. I think this is the biggest challenge teachers face.<BR> CARINE T.<BR> Jakarta <BR>\par \par \uc2 An education system has to make students have stronger character. Meanwhile, our education misses such an important aspect.\par \par \uc2 With the current education system, we only try to explore intelligence quotient (IQ) of the students, not their emotional quotient (EQ).\par \par \uc2 They are treated just like robots without morality. The real example is the current national exams! I think it's a disaster for Indonesia! The system just creates more corruptors.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, the biggest challenge that's facing our education system: How the system can make the nation become a more real human nation that has strong character to meet global challenges.<BR> SRI KEWES<BR> Surabaya <BR>\par \par \uc2 There are a number of problems involving teachers, students, parents and education infrastructure/facilities, which should be addressed:\par \par \uc2 Teachers for students of elementary, junior and senior high schools should hold at least bachelor degree (S1) and for university students, they should have master (S2) or doctoral degrees (S3).\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the education curriculum should be adjusted to the market demand so that all graduates can be accommodated by existing firms/enterprises.\par \par \uc2 The government must improve teachers' welfare. Students should have high discipline and use much of their time to do exercises for their lessons.\par \par \uc2 Their parents must also closely monitor the activities of their children to prevent them from getting involved in bad activities.\par \par \uc2 The government is required to repair damaged school buildings and to provide more educational infrastructure/facilities accordingly.<BR> ABDUL RAHIM<BR> Tangerang, Banten <BR>\par \par \uc2 The government must realize the importance of people education. A country will experience good progress only when the literacy rate is high, which is basic 