\par\par \b \uc2 Parties get behind oil price hike\b0\par\par\uc2 Abdul Khalik , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 601 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 May 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Major political parties are throwing their support behind the government's unpopular plan to raise fuel prices early next month.\par \par \uc2 The United Development Party (PPP), the third-largest faction in the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is the latest party to publicly declare its support for the controversial \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 PPP chairman Suryadharma Ali said Saturday his party understood why the government had to increase fuel prices given the skyrocketing global price of oil.\par \par \uc2 "The oil price surge has placed a huge burden on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  because of much higher \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "We can no longer avoid the issue and maintain the current oil price just to win popularity," Suryadharma, the state minister for small and medium enterprises and cooperatives, told a news conference during the party's national meeting in Jakarta.\par \par \uc2 Other major political groups backing the plan include Vice President Jusuf Kalla's Golkar Party, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono's Democratic Party, the National Mandate Party (PAN) and the Prosperous Justice Party (PKS).\par \par \uc2 Strong opposition has come only from the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P), the party chaired by former president Megawati Soekarnoputri.\par \par \uc2 "The government should find other alternatives before raising fuel prices," PDI-P lawmaker Ganjar Pranowo said.\par \par \uc2 "This proposal breaks Yudhoyono's own political promise (made after he increased fuel prices in 2005)."\par \par \uc2 Gaining the support of most major parties will clear the way for the Yudhoyono administration to go ahead with the plan.\par \par \uc2 The government announced its plan to increase fuel prices to an "affordable" level earlier this month, to allow cuts to burgeoning fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which threaten the sustainability of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 With global oil prices hovering at more than US$120 a barrel, Yudhoyono has faced intense pressure from businesses and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers to cut the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  that keep the domestic prices of gasoline, diesel fuel and kerosene below international market levels.\par \par \uc2 The government earmarked about 12 percent of this year's total national \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , or about Rp 987.48 trillion (US$107 billion), for fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Analysts have warned \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability will harm overseas lending and foreign direct investment and thus weaken the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Funds for infrastructure development, education and health are also likely to be slashed as \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  continues to overwhelm the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Vice President Jusuf Kalla said recently fuel prices would not be increased by more than 30 percent.\par \par \uc2 Golkar lawmaker Harry Azhar Azis, who has played a key role in the oil price hike \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , said prices would be increased by an average of 28.7 percent.\par \par \uc2 Observers have said Yudhoyono would need strong political support from the House to minimize the political fallout from the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and head off widespread \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  demonstrations.\par \par \uc2 Lukman Hakim Saifuddin, the PPP faction chairman at the House, said his party's 58 House members would support the fuel increase provided the government compensated low-income earners to offset the impact of the decision.\par \par \uc2 "We demand a government guarantee to invest more in improving people's incomes to boost their capacity to buy basic commodities and pay for health care and education," he said.\par \par \uc2 The government must also initiate labor-intensive projects that create employment for low-income earners, Lukman said.\par \par \uc2 In voicing support for the plan, PKS lawmaker Mutammimul Ula said the fuel price hike was unavoidable.\par \par \uc2 "The House has not come up with any better alternatives so we have no choice but to increase the prices," he said.\par \par \uc2 PAN legislator Djoko Susilo said his party supported a fuel price hike as a last resort only.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080511e45b0000c\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Measuring Impacts of Fuel Price Hikes, Market to Have Mixed Movement\b0\par\par\uc2 398 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 May 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Market players are estimated to keep their eyes on the government's fuel price hikes \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the impact on inflation. The increasing trend of food prices is worried to boost inflation this year.\par \par \uc2 The Composite Stock Price Index (IHSG) this week is forecasted to have mixed movement and follow the movement of global bourses.\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  companies' actions of publishing their first semester financial statements and of paying dividends are expected to create additional positive sentiments.\par \par \uc2 An analyst at PT Sinarmas Sekuritas Alfiansyah said a combination of domestic and foreign issues would determine the course of market movement this week. The market, he inserted, would keep monitoring global crude oil and price, the impact on inflation, and BI rate projection.\par \par \uc2 "Global crude oil price will put pressures on global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  forces, creating \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the one hand and boosting mining and plantation stocks on the other," he told last weekend.\par \par \uc2 He viewed the market was still speculating over fuel price hikes. The government so far has yet to announce the percentage range of the hike and only said the maximum hikes would be by 30%.\par \par \uc2 Investors anticipated the hikes and probably might sell on news when the government announced the definite percentage range. "The percentage range will become a diving factor."\par \par \uc2 Amid the condition, he added, the index would move between a support point of 2,321 and a resistance point of 2,410. At the trade closing last weekend, the index dropped by 1.91 points to 2,375.027.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, Asian bourses are still under pressures as the Hang Seng index fell by 1.52%, the Seoul index by 1.31%, the KOSPI index by 1.43%, the Shanghai index by 1.19%, Singapore's STI by 0.36%, and the Taiwan index by 0.84%.\par \par \uc2 Foreign investors\par \par \uc2 In the bond market, T-bond prices are steadily increasing, thanks to foreign fund inflow following BI's decision to raise BI benchmark interest rate.\par \par \uc2 The BI rate hike has widened the interest differential rate between BI rate and the Fed Fund rate to 6.25%.\par \par \uc2 "The bond market strengthens because of foreign fund inflow. Foreign investors are attracted to the wide spread," said Assistant Vice President of Fixed Income at PT Bank Danamon Indonesia Tbk Dastin Mudijana as quoted by Bloomberg. (Bisnis/ags)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080512e45c0003h\par }\page {\par\fs20\b  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  Package to be Issued\b0\par\par\uc2 580 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 May 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The government is confirmed to issue at least 38 policies and actions until the end of May and June 2008 in accord with the schedule stated in a follow-up \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  package draft that will be issued soon.\par \par \uc2 "The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  package draft has been handed over by the Coordinating Ministry for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs to the President. The concept of the package has also been approved by the ministers responsible for the action plans," revealed Deputy for Infrastructure Coordination and Regional Development to the Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Bambang Susantono to Bisnis yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs previously stated the government would take several measures before raising subsidized fuel prices, such as by saving fuel and electricity consumption, converting high-cost energy to cheaper one, and providing direct cash assistance as well as people's business credits.\par \par \uc2 In the 2008/2009 follow-up \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  package draft that Bisnis got, most of the policies are on investment improvements (44 actions), followed by those on infrastructures (36), small-medium enterprises (34), and macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and finance (31).\par \par \uc2 Nearly 23% of the total 195 policies and actions are drafted by the Minister of Finance, such as policies on finance, sharia T-bonds, \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , capital investment credit for small-medium enterprises (SMEs), and capital market.\par \par \uc2 Some of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies that will be issued until the end of May and June 2008 are the Special \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Zone Bill, a presidential \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on investment, a revised governmental \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  (PP), a presidential decree on membership of the Zone Council in Batam, Bintan, and Karimun (BBK). (see table).\par \par \uc2 "According to an info that I got, a presidential decree on the Zone Council in Batam, Bintan, and Karimun has been signed. In the meantime, the Special \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Zone Bill has been on the desk of the Department of Justice and Human Rights. It's only one step away from being handed over to the President. By June, the bill will be submitted to the House to be deliberated," continued Bambang.\par \par \uc2 Fuel Blueprint\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, one Bisnis source confided other follow-up \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies were to design port space and logistical road map, design a blueprint for the development of creative \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , draft a blueprint for fuel, make a blueprint for electricity saving, and develop trade partner online database by the second semester of 2008.\par \par \uc2 In addition, the Minister of Energy and Mineral Resources, the State Minister/Head of the National Development Planning Agency (Bappenas), and the Minister of Finance would also sign an MoU to make \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management in the oil and mining sectors more transparent.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, the government would simplify procedures for doing business in the electricity sector, support the 10,000 MW electricity crash program, and allocate \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for rural electricity. Regarding infrastructure development, the government would develop more roads in Java, Kalimantan, and Sulawesi.\par \par \uc2 Several \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies and actions to be taken would be the focus of the 2008-2009 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  program and a continuation of the Presidential Instruction No. 6/2007 on Acceleration of Real Sector and SMEs Empowerment.\par \par \uc2 "The government wants \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development to be on the right track as targeted. The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  package is a continuation of several presidential instructions that had been issued over the past few years," disclosed the source.\par \par \uc2 Another Bisnis source at the Coordinating Ministry for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Services disclosed the package aimed at supporting \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth by improving investments and strengthening export amid \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global situations. (Bisnis/nn/jao)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080514e45e00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
