\par\par \b \uc2 Government confirms re-election of Thaib as N. Maluku governor\b0\par\par\uc2 Ridwan Max Sijabat , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 469 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 June 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 8\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Seven months after the controversial gubernatorial election in North Maluku, the central government on Monday endorsed the re-election of incumbent governor Thaib Armayn and his running mate Abdul Gani Kasuba.\par \par \uc2 Home Minister Mardiyanto said the decision was based on the Supreme Court's March decision to annul the vote count conducted by the General Elections Commission (KPU).\par \par \uc2 "Before making the decision, the central government considered all the legal facts, especially the ones used by the Supreme Court. We also considered political and security factors," he said.\par \par \uc2 The North Maluku gubernatorial election was held in November last year.\par \par \uc2 The vote conflict was triggered by disagreement over the results of vote counting in three districts in the province.\par \par \uc2 A series of violent rallies were staged in North Maluku and outside the Home Ministry in Jakarta protesting the election results. The protests were conducted by Armayn supporters and supporters of Abdul Garfur and his running mate Abdurrahim Fabanyo, who were nominated by the Golkar Party.\par \par \uc2 Security officials responded violently in attempts to stop the rallies, amid fears of a revival of the sectarian conflict that claimed thousands of lives from 2000 to 2002 in North Maluku.\par \par \uc2 The 35-member provincial \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  council was at loggerheads over the election results, with the Golkar faction demanding the government recognize Garfur's victory.\par \par \uc2 On April 12, Coordinating Minister for Political Security and Legal Affairs Widodo A.S. lead a discussion between high-powered government officials, political elites, university academics and religious figures to discuss the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political situation.\par \par \uc2 Following the discussion, Mardiyanto submitted a draft edict to the Supreme Court, which accepted it on May 14, declaring Thaib and Gani the winners of the gubernatorial election.\par \par \uc2 "The Supreme Court awarded the government the discretion to determine the race's winner. We will process the decision and ask the president to issue a decree inaugurating the winning pair who will govern during the 2008-2013 period," Widodo A.S. said.\par \par \uc2 The minister appealed to all sides in North Maluku to accept the decision.\par \par \uc2 He has instructed security authorities to enforce the government's decision and to help reduce conflict to allow the winning pair to focus on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development.\par \par \uc2 Four pairs of governor hopefuls ran for office in the gubernatorial election last year.\par \par \uc2 The incumbent governor and vice governor were nominated by the Democratic Party (PD), the Prosperous Justice Party (PKS) and the Crescent Star Party (PBB).\par \par \uc2 Besides Garfur and Fabanyo, the other candidates were Antony Charles Sunaryo and his running mate Mohammad Amin Drakel, and Irwan Eddyson and his running mate Atti Achmad. Sunaryo and Drakel were nominated by the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan) and Eddyson and Achmad by the Prosperous Peaceful Party (PDS).\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080603e4630000z\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 'BI overnight not optimize OPT'\b0\par\par\uc2 611 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 June 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Some analysts feel pessimistic to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the Overnight inter banks money market (PUAB O/N) in a bid to optimize the open market and stabilize interest rate.\par \par \uc2 The momentum for the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is not on the right time as it is amidst the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the soaring inflation and the \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Indonesia Interest Rate (BI Rate).\par \par \uc2 Ecnomist of \uc2 Bank Rakyat Indonesia\uc2  (BRI) Djoko Retnadi said the momentum for the overnight interest rate implementation should have been done 5-8 months ago when the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and BI Rate was relatively stable if it meant to use the instrument as the latest tool to stabilize monetary.\par \par \uc2 "The response might be belated if the effort of interest rate stabilization is the inflation targeting. This will be difficult due to the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  trend. The ideal implementation should have been on the stable BI Rate of 8 percent," he said to Bisnis in Jakarta last week.\par \par \uc2 Start from today, BI implemented PUAB O/N. the instrument here is deemed the referent for loan inter banks interest with overnight terms on the limitation of BI Rate plus minus by 300 basis points. So, every day there will be change of BI rate of one month period through bidding.\par \par \uc2 The measure is deemed the effort to optimized the open market operation control (OPT) through the purchase of BI Promissory Notes (SBI) with one month within few months have dropped due to the too high yield bidder offer.\par \par \uc2 BI Deputy Governor Budi Mulya said the change of operational target is the effort to anticipate the indirect impact of the fuel price hike and the soaring food commodity prices.\par \par \uc2 "BI will use at best all monetary tools, including BI Rate, foreign exchange rate volatility control, and liquidity excess absorption and OPT optimization and other policies."\par \par \uc2 Upon observing the one month period SBI trend, the interest rate applied in the instrument is not far different from BI Rate of 8.25 percent on May.\par \par \uc2 BI breakthrough\par \par \uc2 Despite his pessimism, Djoko appreciated BI breakthrough through the overnight interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . He wondered whether or not the one month period of instrument effectiveness could be effective.\par \par \uc2 He hoped that the overnight instrument will be able to provide flexibility and market credibility. Unfortunately, the one month SBI tend to move slowly to follow the market fluctuation.\par \par \uc2 "Hopefully it can reduce the monetary burden by pressing down the least minimum interest so as to get the cheapest interest rate efficiency given that our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Other foreign currency fell down, rupiah could even increase," he said.\par \par \uc2 Before BI has given signal for implementing overnight interest rate, some analysts including Director of Bank Lippo Gottfried Tampubolon reminded that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  should completely see the market condition. It is not benefiting for banking industry with the market volatility.\par \par \uc2 "I agree the change to overnight should be done carefully due to the high rate of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Just wait for the better oil price and the market is conducive," he said.\par \par \uc2 Indef economist Aviliani said the implementation of this instrument is not optimum amidst the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  fluctuation, let alone after \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  increased the BI Rate. "Some countries have even dropped the interest rate. But we get more pressures due to the high inflation and soaring BI Rate, I am not sure about the overnight implementation," she said.\par \par \uc2 Head of Treasury \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  Sugiarto gives positive welcome the overnight interest rate implementation despite the quite late if compared to the other countries. "All countries worldwide manage most interest rate through overnight rather than long term period which almost all apply this. (Bisnis/11)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080609e4690000g\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Banking Industry's Foreign Exchange Loan Increases by US$1.01 Billion\b0\par\par\uc2 384 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 June 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Despite the current global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil, the Indonesian banking industry's foreign currency loan as of March 2008 had surged by US$1.01 billion or IDR9.39 trillion (assuming the rupiah exchange rate against the US dollar at IDR9,300) to US$6.01 billion.\par \par \uc2 Data by the \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) showed the total amount of foreign currency loans as of March 2008 had reached US$6,017.44 million, up from US$5,010.59 million in the same period in 2007 and from US$5,400.75 million as of December 2007. (see table)\par \par \uc2 Nevertheless, BI Deputy Governor Hartadi A. Sarwono said such an amount of foreign currency loans was still normal amid the current global situations. "Foreign currency loans are still normal as usual. The yield offered indeed fluctuates," he said recently.\par \par \uc2 When contacted by Bisnis last night, BI Deputy International Director Dian Ediana Rae admitted the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had approved US$1.2 billion worth foreign currency loans for the banking industry. However, Dian continued, so far only US$430 million that had been realized.\par \par \uc2 Overall, added Dian, the banking industry's business plan 2008 recorded US$5.3 billion in foreign currency loans. "Some of the proceeds are for working capitals, investments, and others."\par \par \uc2 Several months ago, the banking industry shifted their foreign-denominated bond to bilateral loans in the wake of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global financial market.\par \par \uc2 Cheaper\par \par \uc2 Financial Director of Bank UOB Buana Syafrullah Hadi Saleh said foreign currency loans offered cheaper interest than rupiah loans, making foreign or composite banks prefer foreign currency bilateral financing.\par \par \uc2 "Amid the surge in domestic interest rate at the moment, the banking industry prefers foreign currency loans. Besides, the foreign currency loans can also be converted to rupiah."\par \par \uc2 Country Business Manager with Citi Markets and Banking Tigor M. Siahaan confirmed its company required more foreign currencies following the rise in export-import needs. "Overall, much of foreign currencies is allocated for the agribusiness and natural resources sectors."\par \par \uc2 An economist at Indef Aviliani asked the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to stay alert for the sharp increase in foreign currency loans amid a global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown and the trend of weaker rupiah exchange rate against foreign currencies, especially against the greenback. (Bisnis/11)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080610e46a00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
