\par\par \b \uc2 The Sri Mulyani-Boediono team\b0\par\par\uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati's concurrent appointment as coordinating minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , replacing Boediono, who has taken over as the new \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor, will maintain, if not strengthen, the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making credibility of President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team.   \par \uc2 725 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 June 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Her appointment, which was made formal Sunday, came as no surprise to anyone. Sri Mulyani's excellent performance in her stint as chair of an inter-ministerial news conference on May 23, to explain the rationale for the fuel price increases, stoked speculation that she would be appointed as acting chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister.\par \par \uc2 Sri Mulyani is the best choice for the position. As minister for development planning from 2004 to late 2005, and finance minister since December 2005, Sri Mulyani has proven her technical skills in managing the macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , notably financial and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  affairs.\par \par \uc2 More importantly, she has proven adept at her job and shown courage, consistency and impeccable integrity in treading the messy politics of development in a newly democratic system like Indonesia's.\par \par \uc2 From the perspective of the international market, Sri Mulyani provides a great degree of stability for Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The Sri Mulyani-Boediono team will surely lend credibility and integrity to the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  management, especially in view of the upcoming parliamentary and presidential elections. Neither are affiliated with any of the political parties, and are the kind of people able to stand up to political pressure for short-term, vested interests.\par \par \uc2 Several politicians and analysts had suggested that the President leave the position of chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister empty, with the presidential election just 18 months away.\par \par \uc2 However, a coordinating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister is still needed because there are several \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform measures that require inter-ministerial coordination for formulating implementation regulations and supervising their execution.\par \par \uc2 Both Sri Mulyani and Boediono will be able to provide strong leadership in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  management, which is badly needed now, given the apparently widening rift and discord between the President and Vice President Jusuf Kalla.\par \par \uc2 In tapping Sri Mulyani, President Yudhoyono must have realized that integrity and competence should be basic assets of his \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team, especially starting next year when government leaders, including himself, the Vice President, who is chairman of Golkar Party, and many other Cabinet ministers will be preoccupied with the agendas of their respective political parties.\par \par \uc2 Under such conditions, a solid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team with integrity and technical competence that commands respect both at home and overseas is needed to manage the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 With Sri Mulyani overseeing \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management and Boediono monetary management, the pair can handle \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  management while other government leaders are busy with their own political ambitions. This is precisely the role Boediono played as finance minister under president Megawati Soekarnoputri during the 2004 general and presidential elections.\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary management face numerous challenges as a result of the impact of the May increase in fuel prices on inflationary expectations, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the international financial market and a weakening global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 However, the government should continue its \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  discipline and push ahead with its reform agenda. Likewise, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  should maintain market trust in its monetary management and in the direction of its monetary policies, particularly during the highly politicized period of the election year.\par \par \uc2 The integrity and credibility of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team could serve as a strong foundation to reassure the market that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  management will remain on the right track during the election year, despite any political pressure for short-term measures to win voter support.\par \par \uc2 The President must, however, protect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team from intervention by vested interests and should see to it that the chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister is really and fully in charge of making and directing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies. It would be better for the unity of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team if the President also replaced Industry Minister Fahmi Idris and State Minister for National Development Planning Paskah Suzetta, both of the Golkar Party.\par \par \uc2 It would be understandable if the pace of reform measures slackened a bit as most members of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  are preoccupied with the upcoming elections. That is simply to be expected in a country engaged in general elections.\par \par \uc2 But as long as \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  consistency and the fundamental elements of macroeconomic stability are maintained, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be able to weather the upcoming period of heightened political emotions.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080617e46h0000m\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Prices of State Bonds to Increase\b0\par\par\uc2 399 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 June 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The prices of state bonds are predicted to increase by five basis points this week following the massive sale and some cornering last week.\par \par \uc2 "The price will recover this week, as the cornering effect has been disappearing and the trading will be back to normal," said an analyst of \uc2 Danareksa Sekuritas\uc2 , Budi Susanto.\par \par \uc2 He said that the euphoria of global bonds also has disappeared and it has caused the decline in prices of sovereign bonds, while foreign investors have been aggressive in bidding the bonds in the primary market.\par \par \uc2 He said foreign investors absorbed IDR5.3 trillion in yesterday's auction.\par \par \uc2 Budi said that the next one week is the best time to get state bonds of medium and long term tenors.\par \par \uc2 "For risk-taker-investors, long term bonds are of good choice," he said. The risk-averter-investors, he said, should buy the medium term ones.\par \par \uc2 He said that the negative sentiment may appear depending on the inflation rate the Central Body of Statistic will announce tomorrow.\par \par \uc2 Contrary to this opinion, the Fund Manager PT Sarijaya Permana Sekuritas Daniel Dwi Seputro said that macro and global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factor, like oil price, will still affect the bond prices this week.\par \par \uc2 The oil price, that has reached US$142 per barrel, is still threatening.\par \par \uc2 "The [negative] effect will be on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and on the concern on whether the government will be able to repay the interest."\par \par \uc2 He said the bond price is good but most investors don't have enough money to buy sovereign bonds as they have invested that much in the instrument.\par \par \uc2 Investors and market players, he said, are closely monitoring on how the government will respond the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the global oil price.\par \par \uc2 "The rumor on the oil price increase of 2% in the next five months is upsetting as it will endanger the political and security stability." He said that the protests against the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will also contribute to the negative sentiment.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime the Director General of Debt Management of Finance Ministry, Rahmat Waluyanto, said that the Fed's decision to maintain the interest rate at 2% could not end the massive sale of global bonds. The point is, he said, that the Fed's decision is consistent and meets the market expectation "so that it will not cause any further turbulence." (Bisnis/21/16)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080701e46u0000k\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
