\par\par \b \uc2 Big cities worst in  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  governance\b0\par\par\uc2 Aditya Suharmoko , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 641 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 July 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Makassar, Yogyakarta, Surabaya and Surakarta were among the major cities whose investment growth last year was hampered by a lack of accessibility and security in land use rights, a survey says.\par \par \uc2 According to the 2007 Local \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governance Index by the regional autonomy watchdog KPPOD, those four cities were among the 10 worst of 243 regencies and cities surveyed in terms of land access and security.\par \par \uc2 The survey, released Tuesday, said the results were surprising as the above cities are known for their relative business savvy and modern infrastructure.\par \par \uc2 In Surabaya, the survey said, investors needed to wait for an average of 36 weeks before a company could acquire a land certificate to start business operations.\par \par \uc2 "About 38.4 percent of respondents took between 11 weeks and more than two years to obtain land certificates," KPPOD chairman Bambang PS Brodjonegoro said during a presentation of survey findings.\par \par \uc2 Land use was just one of nine aspects of local \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  governance studied by the KPPOD for making up this year's index.\par \par \uc2 Other aspects included business licensing, government and business interaction, business development programs, mayor/regent capacity, local \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , user charges and other transaction costs, local infrastructure, security and conflict resolution and local regulations.\par \par \uc2 The KPPOD surveyed 29 business associations and 12,187 firms, 51 percent of which were small businesses.\par \par \uc2 The best-performing district overall was Blitar, a small city of 1.3 million in East Java, which scored high on infrastructure, access to land and licensing.\par \par \uc2 Seven regencies and cities in North Sumatra, including Medan, were among the 10 worst-performing districts in 2007.\par \par \uc2 "Sumatra has legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over land use rights. The government must provide legal certainty ... for projects related to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest," said Muhammad S Hidayat, the chairman of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin).\par \par \uc2 Hidayat said Kadin had sent recommendations on the issuing of land use permits, but the government had not yet responded.\par \par \uc2 In terms of infrastructure, the top indicator in the survey, Indonesian Employers Association (Apindo) chairman Sofjan Wanandi said the government should address electricity problems in regions, as they restricted business growth.\par \par \uc2 "Perhaps regions can cooperate with private companies to build power plants in the areas," Sofjan said.\par \par \uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati said in her opening speech many regions made their own bylaws, which worsened the area's investment climate.\par \par \uc2 "Almost every day the Finance Ministry's Directorate General of Financial Balance recommends canceling or revising two or three bylaws," Mulyani said.\par \par \uc2 As of mid-July, the ministry had evaluated about 7,200 bylaws on regional \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and retribution, 28 percent of which were recommended to be canceled or revised.\par \par \uc2 The Justice and Human Rights Ministry said the government had revoked 974 bylaws since the introduction of regional autonomy in 1999. The ministry has launched a book of guidelines to limit regions in drafting bylaws.\par \par \uc2 The directorate general and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  are also deliberating a bill on regional \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and retribution on fears that regions may be harming investment climate.<br>\par \par \uc2 Overall \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governance Index 2007 <br><br>\par \par \uc2 Top-performing regencies/cities <br> 1. Blitar, East Java<br> 2. Magetan, East Java<br> 3. Prabumulih, South Sumatra<br> 4. Musi Banyuasin, South Sumatra<br> 5. Jembrana, Bali<br> 6. Tuban, East Java<br> 7. Lumajang, East Java<br> 8. Madiun, East Java<br> 9. Probolinggo, East Java<br> 10. Gianyar, Bali<br><br>\par \par \uc2 Worst-performing regencies/cities <br> 1. South Nias, North Sumatra<br> 2. Labuhan Batu, North Sumatra<br> 3. Rokan Hilir, Riau<br> 4. Nias, North Sumatra<br> 5. Rokan Hulu, Riau<br> 6. Bima, West Nusa Tenggara<br> 7. Asahan, North Sumatra<br> 8. Karo, North Sumatra<br> 9. Medan, North Sumatra<br> 10. Tanjung Balai, North Sumatra<br>\par \par \uc2 Source: Regional Autonomy Watch (KPPOD)\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080723e47n00004\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 'President to Deal with Electricity  \highlight22\uc2 Tariff \highlight\uc2  Hike Polemic'\b0\par\par\uc2 321 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 July 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The industries urge President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono to intervene and seek solution to the planned industry electricity \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  hikes.\par \par \uc2 The President's firm stance is also needed to deal with the potentially escalating polemic at the level of labors following the implementation of the joint \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  of five ministers, which shift business and industry working days to Saturday-Sunday.\par \par \uc2 Lack of a firm stance will curb business climate and make it difficult to realize \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and industry growth targets.\par \par \uc2 Chairperson of the Association of Indonesian Synthetic Fiber Producers (Apsyfi) Kustarjono Prodjolalito asked President Yudhoyono to give the best solution to deal with the problem.\par \par \uc2 "We appeal to Pak SBY's [Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono] wisdom in dealing with electricity crisis," he said yesterday.\par \par \uc2 The Indonesia Textile Association (API) and the Indonesian Employers Association (Apindo) also urge the government to revise the joint \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  of five ministers, which had yet regulated overtime.\par \par \uc2 "In the joint \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , there are several technical issues that have yet been agreed to and are still being discussed. At the same time, we are still waiting for a circulation letter from the Department of Manpower and Transmigration on the elimination of overtime pay," said Chairperson of the Indonesian Employers Association (Apindo) Sofjan Wanandi yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Chairperson of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Monetary Industry Permanent Committee at the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) Bambang Soesatyo called for President Yudhoyono to understand the employers' problems and not to let the polemic go on for months since it could create business climate \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "The President is expected to instruct an audit of state electricity company PLN. The President will be able to fix the hike range based on the audit," he told Bisnis yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Kadin, he added, agreed that industry electricity tariffs should be adjusted with their \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  level. "However, it will be inappropriate to raise industry electricity tariffs this year." (Bisnis/yuw)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080728e47s00005\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
