\par\par \b \uc2 President asks local govts not to abuse autonomy\b0\par\par\uc2 Desy Nurhayati , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 541 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 August 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 While praising the flourishing democracy in regions as a result of direct elections, the President asked local administrations on Friday to be mindful of exercising their authority only for the sake of people's welfare.\par \par \uc2 During his speech at the plenary session of the Regional Representatives Council (DPD), Yudhoyono said the central government had delegated part of its duties to local administrations both in politics and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  matters to help them enhance \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  services and propel development.\par \par \uc2 "Under decentralization, there is no such thing as a single level of government dominating all control. Part of the authority that has been entrusted to provincial and municipal administrations should be for the sake of people's welfare, not for the administration's well-being," he said.\par \par \uc2 The delegation of power includes a bigger portion of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and revenue sources given to the regional governments, as well as the implementation of a direct election system to select leaders.\par \par \uc2 Since the first direct regional election in June 2005, the country has seen 414 elections of governors, regents and mayors.\par \par \uc2 "A great transformation of politics has taken place in our country in the last couple of years with the improvement of democracy at the local level. This process is ongoing, and we have succeeded in conducting it effectively and peacefully," Yudhoyono said.\par \par \uc2 "This has automatically changed the nation's political map and enhanced our rhythm of politics to be more accountable and democratic. But we continue to evaluate the regional election system to eliminate any shortcomings, as well as to prepare for next year's general election."\par \par \uc2 The President's statement contradicted the earlier speech of DPD Speaker Ginandjar Kartasasmita, who expressed concern the host of regional elections would burden the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "There has been indication of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  apathy," Ginandjar said of the regional elections. Across the country, local elections held this year saw low voter turnout.\par \par \uc2 Ginandjar asked the government to consider a review of direct elections.\par \par \uc2 "If the benefit equals the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , we can understand (direct regional elections) to be the cost of democracy. But if not, they are a waste of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Ginandjar said.\par \par \uc2 The DPD session comes a week after the President delivered a state of the union address at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The speech at the DPD has been a regular fixture in national politics since the inception of the representative body in 2004.\par \par \uc2 All DPD members and government officials attending the session, including Vice President Jusuf Kalla and Cabinet ministers, were dressed in batik.\par \par \uc2 Unlike the House plenary session, the DPD has always added an artistic touch to its annual session. On Friday a performance by musician Elfa Secoria opened the event.\par \par \uc2 Both the government and the DPD were of the opinion that regional autonomy had sparked conflicts between central and local regulations.\par \par \uc2 "Based on the DPD's evaluation, the problems include inconsistency between the decentralization policies and other laws and regional regulations. This has caused an overlapping of regulations in regions that results in legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Ginandjar said.\par \par \uc2 He said the council demanded the government arrange a clearer roadmap toward a better system of autonomy, which the President accepted.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080823e48n00004\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
