\par\par \b \uc2 BI strives to control inflationary trends to keep RI buoyant\b0\par\par\uc2 894 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 September 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  poses a threat to Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, with the risk of inflation, not only from the supply side but from the demand side, forcing policymakers to rethink strategy on how to weather the storm.\par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post' s Rendi Akhmad Witular recently talked with the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor for monetary affairs Budi Mulya on the current state of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Here are some excerpts from the interview:\par \par \uc2 Question : What is the most threatening factor to our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ? Answer : What we are facing right now is pressure on prices, that is, inflation.\par \par \uc2 While inflation is a global phenomenon, in Indonesia inflation was being triggered initially by supply side problems. There are supply side rigidities as a result of which costs of industrial production are rising due to the impact of soaring prices for global energy and raw materials\par \par \uc2 Our inflation was more on this type until early last year when there were strong indications that inflation was also being driven by demand side issues. For example, higher \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth led to the expansion of money supply above normal levels, as well as rapid increases in the sales of cars and motorcycles.\par \par \uc2 Even though there was an increase in fuel prices (in late May), our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was shown to be fundamentally strong, evidenced by the continuing increases in sales and in demand for loans. This is very different from conditions back in 2005, when the government increased the fuel prices.\par \par \uc2 The situation was similar at that time, but the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals today are much stronger, supported by rapidly rising demand from areas outside Java, which are benefitting from increased commodity prices.\par \par \uc2 Demand in Java and Jakarta is robust as well, with growth in the manufacturing sector, despite increasing costs.\par \par \uc2 Lending has grown rapidly thus far. How sustainable is it?\par \par \uc2 Lending growth is high. \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) requires all banks to implement their risk management analysis. Banks should exercise this as part of ensuring that they are more prudent. We also want to make sure that bank liquidity is sufficient.\par \par \uc2 How do you see the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the second half?\par \par \uc2 Overall, growth for this year will be lower than in 2007. We expect growth to reach above 6 percent but below the 6.3 percent recorded in 2007\par \par \uc2 From the monetary aspect, because we see that inflation is now being driven by the demand side, we will focus on applying a tighter monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We have already tackled this with several instruments, including interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , currency intervention and liquidity management.\par \par \uc2 Other countries may focus their measures on currency, but we are still focusing our attention on interest rate measures. If we don't raise the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , then we are not reinforcing the expectation of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  certainty. Expectations are an abstract idea. If we think inflation will reach 15 percent and we don't act to constrain it, then it will probably happen. So there should be a common expectation between the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  and stakeholders. There should be a commitment from us.\par \par \uc2 Can the BI rate move in alignment with demand from the business sector (of not more than 9.5 percent)?\par \par \uc2 The business community has complained about the current interest rate. But the base rate is just one among the factors determining the success of a company in posting a profit. Soaring energy prices are also a reason for some companies to post a profit.\par \par \uc2 We should make sure that BI raises the interest rate just to control the inflation. If we do nothing, inflation will accelerate to double digits because of the absence of a pillar of stability. This would in turn create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the business community.\par \par \uc2 How do you see the volatility in the rupiah?\par \par \uc2 Regional currencies share similar features. This is a global phenomenon because the United States dollar is strengthening against other currencies. This situation (currency depreciation) is not a monopoly of emerging markets, but is also present in Europe and Japan. So this is a global storm. The rupiah is not depreciating lower than other currencies. I would like to emphasize the recent volatility in the rupiah is not triggered by fundamental domestic factors.\par \par \uc2 Has hot money played any role in the recent rupiah plunge?\par \par \uc2 Portfolio investors are seeking security and higher yields as reflected by macro stability. There is an inflow of short-term portfolio funds into our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as can be seen in the rising number of rupiah-denominated assets owned by foreign investors, especially in the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  depository certificates (SBI) and in government bonds.\par \par \uc2 The amount of foreign funds coming into SBIs has increased significantly. Currently, foreign investors have financed one third of the SBIs.\par \par \uc2 But for BI, the most important thing is to give them confidence in Indonesia. If the investors feel secure, they will move to higher-yield instruments, such as government bonds, which are more liquid and can be traded in the secondary market.\par \par \uc2 BI and the government must ensure macro stability to keep the investors comfortable in putting their money here.\par \par \uc2 How do you see 2009 then? It will be better than 2008. Growth can reach above 6.1 percent while inflation can ease back to between 6.5 percent and 7.5 percent. This is taking into account the impact of the general election.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080910e49a0001g\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Small bank more skillful to manage  \highlight22\uc2 public \highlight\uc2  fund\b0\par\par\uc2 561 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 September 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Leading banks are facing liquidity hardship due to the fact that they rely on the fund saved in the monetary instrument. But small medium banks could survive better to use the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds.\par \par \uc2 Deputy Governor of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Indonesia (BI) Hartadi A. Sarwono said the small medium banks could survive better amidst the competition for getting liquidity noting that they have so far relied on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  fund to disburse loan.\par \par \uc2 "If we observe, the small bank has no problems, given that they don't have promissory notes such as SUN (government bonds) and SBI (BI promissory notes) and rely on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  fund," he said this week.\par \par \uc2 The small medium bank provides quite attractive deposit interest rate to the market shares so that they survive for loan expansion.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, major bank relies more on the promissory notes ownership in their business expansion. When it is hard to get liquidity, they get the fund from it.\par \par \uc2 "Major banks relies more on promissory notes possession such as SBI and SUN."\par \par \uc2 In the past eight months, bank fund placed in the SBI dropped IDR142 trillion into IDR98 trillion. The position of total SBI owned by banks and non banks currently stand at IDr164 trillion as from IDR284 trillion earlier last year.\par \par \uc2 But BI data in August, the average banks withdrawing SBI is the 10 major banks. The SBI of 10 leading banks in the past eight months stands at IDR79.5 trillion or 67 percent as from IDR118.8 trillion last year.\par \par \uc2 Bank fund for the business expansion capital which is saved in the government bonds (SUN) now is hampered by the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition which bet the yield of the instrument here.\par \par \uc2 "SUN can be sold or repurchased order, but due to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition, the SUN price will inflict loss if sold. Worse, bank only has SUN. that is the reason for the more tightened liquidity for some banks," he said.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  therefore intends to facilitate the repurchase order, bonds divestment which could be repurchased by the banks so that they can serve as the bank liquidity resources. Hartadi, however, has no idea of the time for the implementation.\par \par \uc2 "The repo facilities from the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the promissory notes should go along well so as to help reduce the risk for promissory notes holders. It means, it could be deposited to the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  and they can take it any time."\par \par \uc2 But the tightened liquidity, as to him, is due not only to the dependency to the SBI and SUN, bur rather by the realization of the government \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  which come from \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  is not disbursed directly to fund the real sector development\par \par \uc2 "The government should have spent the fund (of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) for the development. But the government \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still limited so that the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains withheld. This makes the liquidity tightened."\par \par \uc2 Director of Bank Negara Indonesia (BNI) Bien Subiantoro said the major bank will not get difficulty to have liquidity let alone the fund in the form of SBI is getting down in amount.\par \par \uc2 If SBI fund is getting limited, the major banks will target the fund from \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . "The drop of SBI will move it to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  fund and there is now interest rate war," he said to Bisnis yesterday. (Bisnis/11)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080910e49a0000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
