\par\par \b \uc2 Prime to go ahead with IPO\b0\par\par\uc2 Ika Krismantari , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 352 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 September 2008\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 14\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Integrated oil and gas service provider \uc2 PT Prime Petroservices\uc2  (PPS) will stick to its plan to publicly offer 30 percent of its stake next month despite \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the stock market.\par \par \uc2 After a two-month delay, PPS is optimistic the initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering (IPO) will take place in early October, once the company secures a permit from the stock market regulator.\par \par \uc2 Under the IPO plan, the company will sell 1.78 billion new shares at Rp 205 (2 U.S. cents) a share.\par \par \uc2 "We believe the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's fundamentals are still doing great. That's why we're upbeat about proceeding with the plan," PPS finance director Didit A. Ratam told The Jakarta Post on Monday.\par \par \uc2 PPS expects to rake in nearly Rp 360 billion from the IPO proceeds, with some 90 percent being used to help finance its liquefied natural gas (LNG) project while the remaining 10 percent goes toward working capital.\par \par \uc2 The company plans to build a Rp 3 trillion LNG plant this year on Pagerungan Island, north of Bali, with a total capacity of 300,000 tons per year.\par \par \uc2 According to PPS, the new plant will be Indonesia's fourth, after Bontang in East Kalimantan, Arun in Nanggroe Aceh Darussalam and an ongoing Tangguh project in Papua, scheduled to go online by the end of the year.\par \par \uc2 PT Madani Securities, PT Ciptadana Securities and PT Recapital Securities have been appointed as the underwriter for the IPO.\par \par \uc2 PT Eclipse Pacific Service owns 79 percent of PPS, with 9.8 percent held by PT Barata Makmur Abadi and the remaining portion split between several companies.\par \par \uc2 The company expects to list its shares on the Indonesian Stock Exchange (IDX) on Oct. 15, making it the 19th company to go \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year. The IDX hopes to have a total of 30 companies offering IPO's in 2008.\par \par \uc2 The Composite Index has shed more than 10 percent since last week following a combination of worries, particularly a decline in commodity prices that has the potential to dampen the commodity-heavy \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020080916e49g0001f\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Govt yet Intended to Lower Fuel Prices\b0\par\par\uc2 576 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 September 2008\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2008 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Pessimism toward the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  abounds, lowering global crude oil price to its seven-month low of US$92 per barrel. However, the government has yet had any intention to correct subsidized domestic fuel prices after it raised the prices by an average of 30% on May 24.\par \par \uc2 The US and global financial crises, marked with the losses of at least 11 financial institutions affected by the sub-prime mortgage crisis, have slowed down demand for crude oil and other commodities.\par \par \uc2 Oil price fell by 4.3% yesterday after \uc2 Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc\uc2 , the fourth largest investment bank in the US, filed for bankruptcy.\par \par \uc2 "This is a widespread panic. Everyone is thinking the world is on the verge of bankruptcy and there will be no more demand for crude oil," said Jonathan Kornafel, Director of Asia-based Hudson Capital Energy in Singapore yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Yesterday on the \uc2 New York Mercantile Exchange\uc2 , oil price for October shipment fell by 4.3% or US$4.15 to US$91.56 per barrel.\par \par \uc2 At 13:17 the Singaporean time, oil price stayed at US$91/80 per barrel, the lowest since February 11 and down from its record high of US$147.27 per barrel on July 11.\par \par \uc2 Morgan Stanley\uc2  even projected oil price would keep declining if Barrack Obama won the US presidential race.\par \par \uc2 "If the candidate from the Democrat Party wins the election, there is a 66% chance oil price will decline, while if it is the candidate from the Republic Party who wins the election, there is only a 44% chance oil price will decline," told David M. Darst, Managing Director and Chief Investment Strategist of \uc2 Morgan Stanley\par \par \uc2 At home, the government has yet had any intention to lower domestic fuel prices despite the declining global crude oil price. Vice President Jusuf Kalla stated even if oil price fell to US$90 per barrel, the government still had to spend IDR100 trillion on fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 When fuel prices were raised four months ago, global crude oil was traded at US$131.79 per barrel.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, Minister of Finance Sri Mulyani Indrawati told the government would calculate the ideal oil prices amid the current global turbulence and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 She argued the impacts of the US financial crisis on the government were bigger than predicted, leading directly to interest rate hike and declining commodity prices potential to revise assumptions in the 2009 Revised State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "We don't expect the magnitude of the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be as extraordinary as today," she inserted in Jakarta yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Rupiah fares better\par \par \uc2 Sri Mulyani added Indonesia still fared well, thanks to the good rupiah exchange rate against the US dollar compared to other currencies. The rupiah exchange rate against the US dollar had only been deprecated by less than one digit.\par \par \uc2 "Our rupiah has only been depreciated by 0.8% in year to date, while other currencies have been depreciated worse than the rupiah," she said.\par \par \uc2 She continued the Korean won had been depreciated by 19%, the Indian rupee by 15%, the Thailand Baht by 13%, and the Philippine peso by 12.7%. "The currencies of Malaysia and Australia have also been depreciated by 4.3% and 8.7%, respectively."\par \par \uc2 The Minister of Finance believed there would be a solution to the current tight liquidity. "Once we reach the equilibrium, things will be back to normal." (Bisnis/htr/11/16/23/esu/jao)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020080917e49h00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
