 other hand, a conflicting market reaction might trigger several legislators from the Republic Party to change their minds.\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2 In response to the Bill approval, Indonesian Minister of Finance Sri Mulyani Indrawati argued the bailout plan tug-of-war had created \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  worldwide. She added that any decision or statement made by the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary authorities in the US would create sentiments affecting market players worldwide.\par \par \uc2 "This is a crisis that needs a long-term solution. As a result, the impacts on the world will also be relatively long," she said when celebrating Idul Fitri on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 She explained the effects of the US financial crisis on Indonesia were not as huge as those on other countries. The monetary situation, domestic bank condition, and 2008 Revised State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  posture were still good in terms of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and balance of payment.\par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono in the meantime called for developed countries, especially the US, to take swift and proper actions to deal with the financial crisis.\par \par \uc2 Head of the Capital Market and Financial Institution Supervisory Agency (Bapepam-LK) Ahmad Fuad Rahmany disclosed the US bailout plan was worth taken to prevent the financial crisis from affecting the global financial sector. "If there is no bailut, we will face the worst-case scenario."\par \par \uc2 In line with Fuad, President Director of the Indonesia Stock Exchange (BEI) Erry Firmansyah disclosed the financial market condition at the moment was \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , leading the BEI to suspend short-selling actions.\par \par \uc2 Short-selling is shares sale transaction made by investors who don't have the shares. To do this, securitie